org.opensaml.messaging.decoder

Interface MessageDecoder<MessageType>

  • Type Parameters:
    MessageType - the message type of the message context on which to operate
    All Superinterfaces:
    net.shibboleth.utilities.java.support.component.Component, net.shibboleth.utilities.java.support.component.DestructableComponent, net.shibboleth.utilities.java.support.component.InitializableComponent
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    HttpClientResponseMessageDecoder<MessageType>, HttpServletRequestMessageDecoder<MessageType>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractHttpClientResponseMessageDecoder, AbstractHttpServletRequestMessageDecoder, AbstractMessageDecoder, BaseHttpClientResponseXMLMessageDecoder, BaseHttpServletRequestXMLMessageDecoder

    public interface MessageDecoder<MessageType>
extends net.shibboleth.utilities.java.support.component.InitializableComponent, net.shibboleth.utilities.java.support.component.DestructableComponent
    Interface for component that decodes message data from a source into a MessageContext. Before the decoder can be used the InitializableComponent.initialize() method must be called. After the decoder has been used the DestructableComponent.destroy() method should be invoked in order to clean up any resources.

    The data on which the decoder operates is supplied in an implementation-specific manner.
